{
  "texts": [
    "To evaluate the eligibility of the electrodes and the timewindow that SHERPA produced, a cluster-based permutation analysis of the EEG data is performed.",
    "It provides a solution for the multiple comparison problem that is particularly present in data-driven EEG analysis and thus is progressively used in EEG research (see e.g., Tagliabue et al., 2019; Urigüen, Garcia-Zapirain, Artieda, Iriarte, & Valencia, 2017).",
    "In cluster-based permutation tests firstly a test statistic is computed for every electrode and time point and then neighboring ones are clustered applying a predefined threshold.",
    "Permutations are computed on the clusters thereby decreasing the number of tests and hence the risk of false positives.",
    "However, spatial resolution is sacrificed in the process."
  ]
}